  <h2 id="gacha">Gacha</h2>
  <HR />
  <p>
    <i
      >See also:
      <WikiLink page="Construction">Construction</WikiLink></i
    >
  </p>

  <p>
    Wisdom Cubes should only be used on Event banners, indicated by the text
    that says <b>EVENT</b> when choosing a build pool. The Event build pool also
    contains permanent pool ships alongside the rate-up Event ships.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <p>
        You should be completing the
        <WikiLink page="Missions#Daily Missions">Daily Mission</WikiLink>
        "Build 1 ship" by building 1 ship from Light Construction. The mission gives
        you your Cube back, making it a net-zero Cube loss.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        It is not recommended to build on any other Construction Pools, even for
        the Daily Mission, but its your cubes to lose.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <br />

  <h2 id="rerolling">Rerolling</h2>
  <HR />
  <p>
    It is not recommended to reroll accounts due to the cube income being spread
    out instead of frontloaded, especially at the start of the game.
  </p>
  <p>
    The only exception is if you are starting during a UR event, where the UR
    ship is a rate-up ship in the Event banner.
  </p>
  <br />

  <h2 id="hard_mode_cheese">
    <WikiLink page="Combat#Hard Mode">Hard Mode</WikiLink> Cheese
  </h2>
  <HR />
  <p>
    You can cheese a 3-star <WikiLink page="Combat#Hard Mode"
      >Hard Mode</WikiLink
    > clear due to the map mechanics.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        First, kill all the mobs, then kill the boss.
        <b>(2 stars, 1 attempt)</b>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Second, kill all the mobs you can, but before killing the boss, leave
        the stage. This doesn't use up an attempt. Repeat until you obtain the
        last star, then either kill the boss again (using up the daily attempt)
        or retreat. <b>(1 stars, 0 attempts)</b>
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
  <p>
    If you do not see mobs upon entry, be sure to
    <b>turn Clearing Mode off</b>.
  </p>
